caption: Gluten free me!!!!i love ordering takeout from here

Such a clean and open atmosphere. Food was quick and great and staff was awesome! Definitely a good place to go with friends, on a date, or with family! Or by yourself, too! Good selection of gluten free food in Brooklyn.
Perfect place for brunching with friends. When I come home to bay ridge brooklyn I always meet my friend here for Sunday brunch. We catch up over a great cup of coffee and exquisite food!

So many great healthy options on their menu to chose from. I got the smashed Avocado heirloom tomato and poached egg on toast-- it was very tasty. My wife the eggs benedict with smoked salmon and she said it was the best she has ever had.

Taking into consideration the serving time, the quality of the dishes, and the fact they have healthy lunch varieties, I would rate this little café at 5 stars. I am quite impressed by the waiters, and by the cooks as well.

Brooklyn people, this café is amazing! Give it a try if you don't want something overcrowded and with high prices. You will feel like home and the staff will make sure you really enjoy your time there.

My coworkers and I always have lunch here. I love their "Chicken liver mousse, pickled onions, charred bread". There are plenty of options available and the daily menu is large and cheap. We are all very happy to give this place a 5 star rating.

If you are in Brooklyn, I suggest you try this small restaurant. The healthy lunches are great and very cheap. Everything is fresh, so they definitely check the quality of their products. Excellent service.

For healthy food, this is the best choice. They really take great care with the ingredients. I am a pretty demanding person, yet they managed to meet and even exceed my expectations. Delicious roasted baby beets!

Wow, who would have thought?! This is a pretty small place, with just a couple of tables. However, you will always find a table for you here. Few people know about this Bay Ridge cafe... But for a healthy snack, it's the best!

This is the only place we eat out in Brooklyn. Why? I really don't know. Probably because the staff is always with a big smile on their faces and the food tastes great. The lunch is always healthy and has very little grease.

The cheapest and coziest cafe in Brooklyn! A little hidden gem! My family loved them and their Fire roasted tomato bisque. We will surely visit again whenever we are in the Bay Ridge area. I recommend them!!!

It's a little place, but not the small. I agree, there is nothing special about it. But I really love the atmosphere and the service. Also, I found that their healthy lunch and snacks are very tasty. The prices are relatively cheap.
